    "causal_summary": "The 029 model benchmark caught an off-corpus term scoring good on a lone spurious high-cosine hit, and the 005 improvement research traced it to a score-calibration miss in the banding seam rather than an envelope-fidelity miss. The band reads the pre-calibration absolute relevance with no grounding signal, no background-cosine subtraction, no caveat tier, and no evidence-gap bridge, so a fluent but unrelated doc that earns a high background cosine reaches good. This phase hardens that seam around the convergent root-cause fix. It surfaces a grounding signal so a downgrade is legible, subtracts a measured corpus noise-floor before banding so the background cosine no longer inflates the band, adds a cite_with_caveat tier so borderline grounding is hedged rather than dropped, bridges stage4.evidenceGapDetected into the verdict so a known gap lowers the band, and documents the calibration re-fit as a proven non-fix because banding is taken off the pre-calibration value and the curve cannot move the verdict. Every behavioral change ships behind a default-OFF flag and graduates only against the off-corpus fixtures, with a grandfather report for the legacy fixtures the new contract rejects.",
